&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Yext (NYSE: YEXT) is the enterprise agentic marketing platform. AI is changing how customers find brands, and Yext gives enterprises the infrastructure to compete: Scout analyzes 10 billion signals monthly across four AI models to surface where you&#39;re losing and why, the Knowledge Graph maintains the verified data AI cites, and content generation and distribution agents syndicate brand content across LLMs, listings, social platforms, and review sites in real time. Thousands of brands in financial services, healthcare, retail, hospitality, and food rely on Yext to win across AI and traditional search. Join us and experience firsthand why we are consistently recognized as a Best Place to Work globally by Built In, Fortune, and Great Place To Work®.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an &lt;strong&gt;Associate Technical Partner Manager&lt;/strong&gt; (ATPM) at Yext, you will support, maintain, optimize, and expand a portfolio of integrations across the Yext Publisher Network. You will troubleshoot integration issues, contribute to the onboarding of new publishers, monitor and analyze system health data, and work with internal teams and publisher partners to improve integration health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a technical, hands-on role that goes beyond traditional operations work. ATPMs write code to handle configuration updates, test fixes, and small improvements with the help of AI coding tools. You will also help shape integration changes by investigating issues, clarifying requirements, and writing specs that Engineering builds from.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work on scoped problems with guidance from senior team members, and grow toward owning larger projects independently. The ideal candidate is technical, organized, detail-oriented, and eager to learn, with strong problem-solving skills, a passion for data analysis, APIs, and integrations, and curiosity about what AI tools make possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Publisher Integration &amp;amp; Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a portfolio of publisher integrations, accountable for their continued health, and contribute meaningfully to the support of tier 1 publishers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor integration health using SQL, Snowflake, Python, Grafana, dashboards, and system logs; identify discrepancies and drive their resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute meaningfully to the onboarding of new publishers, following established workflows and suggesting process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and troubleshoot data sync and display issues, exploring documentation and available tools before escalating.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;QA and test new fields, features, and integrations with guidance from senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Troubleshooting &amp;amp; AI-Assisted Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write integration-specific&amp;nbsp; code using AI coding tools like Claude Code (configuration updates, test fixes, and small improvements), submitted through code review with senior guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read and write scripts (Python preferred) to automate monitoring and troubleshooting tasks, reducing manual work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write complex SQL queries against Snowflake to identify trends and surface insights on integration health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze API responses, data pipelines, and system logs to diagnose issues and identify root cause within your publisher area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop expertise in at least one tool or system beyond your publisher network (e.g., Snowflake, Gerrit, Grafana, Jenkins).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Communication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Yext (NYSE: YEXT) is the enterprise agentic marketing platform. AI is changing how customers find brands, and Yext gives enterprises the infrastructure to compete: Scout analyzes 10 billion signals monthly across four AI models to surface where you&#39;re losing and why, the Knowledge Graph maintains the verified data AI cites, and content generation and distribution agents syndicate brand content across LLMs, listings, social platforms, and review sites in real time. Thousands of brands in financial services, healthcare, retail, hospitality, and food rely on Yext to win across AI and traditional search. Join us and experience firsthand why we are consistently recognized as a Best Place to Work globally by Built In, Fortune, and Great Place To Work®.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yext is searching for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Billing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Analyst &lt;/strong&gt;to join our growing India Operations Center as part of the global Finance Team. The Billing Team handles a wide range of responsibilities, including daily invoice processing and collaboration with account managers and customers to address any billing inquiries. This position shares the responsibility for handling day-to-day billing operations for new and existing products, managing high-volume client inquiries and transactional processing, and supporting billing project initiatives. Reports to the Manager, Billing Operations based in IOC.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
