&lt;li&gt;Execute daily invoicing for standard contracts and amendments, ensuring accuracy across multi-currency and regional formatting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process credit memos, refunds, chargebacks, account upgrades, and terminations in a timely and accurate manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain operational knowledge of billing systems to ensure client configurations for billing and fulfillment are accurate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Collections team to research and resolve invoice disputes that are delaying payment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all billing activities and record-keeping via tickets adhere to internal audit controls and SOX compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee sales tax and VAT compliance, including the end-to-end management of exemption certificates and regular audits of customer invoices to ensure tax accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in regular data clean-up projects to ensure all billing records and account data are kept accurate and up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Senior Billing Analyst and Revenue department with monthly reconciliation efforts, including tracking invoice data and identifying irregularities for review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work within cross-functional teams to resolve billing errors and provide feedback to internal teams on reconciliation progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
